    Computes the data structure for the Hovmoller plots using a stars object as input

    hovmoller.stars.Rd

    This function creates the data structure for Hovmoller plots for either latitude or longitude.

    Usage

    # S3 method for stars
hovmoller(x, lat_or_lon = "lat", xlen = NULL, ...)

    Arguments

    x

    A stars object or a dataframe. Arguments differ according to the input type.

    lat_or_lon

    Needs to be either lat or lon. lat plots the latitudinal Hovmoller plat, while lon plots the longitudinal Hovmoller plot.

    xlen

    The length of the xaxis for latitude/longitude.

    ...

    Other arguments that need to be used for datafames or currently ignored.

    Examples

    library(stars)
prec_file = system.file("nc/test_stageiv_xyt.nc", package = "stars")
prec <- read_ncdf(prec_file)
#> no 'var' specified, using Total_precipitation_surface_1_Hour_Accumulation
#> other available variables:
#>  lat, lon, time
#> Will return stars object with 236118 cells.
#> No projection information found in nc file. 
#>  Coordinate variable units found to be degrees, 
#>  assuming WGS84 Lat/Lon.
hov <- hovmoller(prec)
hov
